Vice President Joe Biden and Department of Agriculture Secretary Tom Vilsack will be traveling to North Carolina on April 1st to highlight the impact of the Recovery Act on rural America. They will be visiting the Goshen Medical Center in Faison, which has received funds from the Recovery Act and serves several counties. They will also visit the Rural Fire Department in Pikeville, which is receiving funds to build a new facility. Additionally, Biden and Vilsack will be making a major announcement regarding rural housing funding. Further details on the trip and media logistics will be released soon.